==Portuguese==

===Etymology===
most probably from the [[Tupi]] native South American language ''Kaa-boc'', meaning "one who has got the colour of copper"

===Proper noun===
'''Caboclo'''

# (''Brazilian'') a South American descended from the indigenous peoples of Brazil. Also, a Brazilian of mixed Caucasian and Native American or Native American and African ancestry. Used specially to refer to people living in the Amazon Rain Forest.